description: Innsmouth is a dark and creepy place, brimming with a rich history of magic and evil. Lawrence Talbot is an adjuster who has set up shop in Innsmouth, and he isn't quite prepared when the fat man comes into his office and tells him that the world may be ending and that a certain lupine creature may be the Elder Gods' instrument of destruction. Now, whether he wants to be involved or not, Lawrence is embroiled in the malevolence that is running through the town, and may himself be the werewolf in question.
name: Neil Gaiman's Only the End of the World Again

description: Welcome to the first stop in your tour of Comics' Greatest World -- Arcadia, a city where, if you don't play by the rules, you might be the next corpse. Larry Briggs found that out -- right before his insides got sprayed all over the nice walls of his high-rise office. Now the law is looking for the man responsible, and the law in Arcadia is big, thick-skinned, and vicious. But no one's going to find X until he wants to be found. And when that happens, everyone's going to be sorry.
name: X
Pit Bulls

description: Someone brutally murdered Ghost, and she's not happy about it. She's an apparition with an attitude, a taste for revenge, and nothing to lose. Anyone who crosses her is likely to end up dead. That includes X -- he makes the mistake of going after a man whose life Ghost wants for herself. He finds out the hard way that it's tough to crush the bones of someone who doesn't have any, it's tough to blow someone to bits when they have no substance, and it's tough to kill someone who's already dead.  X also finds out that Ghost has some nasty habits. And two of them are Colt .45s.
name: Ghost

description:
Overview

Life on the streets of Arcadia is rough enough, but under the streets, it's rougher than anyone could imagine -- anyone human, that is! But the sewers are home to rats, refuse, renegades, and a monster... a monster of limitless strength and all-consuming anger... a monster who swats bullets away like mosquitoes and tosses two-hundred-pound men aside like bags of garbage. It doesn't mean to split the bags apart... usually. Just don't make the monster mad.
name: Monster

description:
Overview

She's blonde, beautiful, and bad to the bone -- she's Barb Wire, bounty hunter with an attitude. The savage streets of Steel Harbor are ruled by human predators with prices on their heads. The highest price comes for the bad boys with super powers, and big game is Barb's specialty. But when the events in Golden City set off a firestorm of violence in Steel Harbor's urban jungle, Barb finds herself in danger of being burned alive -- literally!
name: Barb Wire
Wolf Gang
Motorhead
Division 13

description:
Overview

David MacRae is like any normal thirteen-year-old boy, except that in addition to skateboards and schoolbooks, David is in telepathic contact with the mysterious entity known as Zero. While unimaginable chaos breaks loose at Cinnabar Flats, Zero wakes David in the dead of night and leads him out into the desert -- just in time for David to transform into Hero Zero and face the biggest, most bizarre battle of his life!
name: Hero Zero
Out of the Vortex
Rebel

description:
Overview

He's huge, he's powerful, and he's encased in alien technology! His name is Mecha, he's a newcomer to Golden City, and this is his big chance to show Grace he can come out on top and still fighting even against the likes of Warmaker. Brute strength against brute strength, the two are almost equally matched -- like locomotives in a head-on collision. Warmaker has a few surprises; but then Mecha surprises himself... Maybe his armor has capabilities even he hasn't dreamed of!
name: Mecha

description:
Overview

With the kind of raw power that the ancients used to whisper about in myths, it's no wonder they call him Titan. But he's no myth, and he's in for the fight of his life! Titan: as hard as concrete, almost as fast as the missiles Warmaker can launch out of his own skin, and a lot smarter than the average grunt. But is he smart enough to realize he may have underestimated his opponent?
name: Titan

description:
Overview

Warmaker is out of control, and the better part of Grace's Golden City lies in ruins because of him. It's time for the amazing Grace to step in with Catalyst, her hand-picked, super-powered agents of change, to set things right. There are tough questions facing Grace, and she's prepared with tough answers. But the most nagging question may never be answered: Did Grace engineer the Warmaker dilemma just so she could step in and fix it?
name: Catalyst
Sky Masters of the Space Force
Sky Masters of the Space Force

description: Back Issue ushers in Spring with some of comics' funniest 'April Fools'! Keith Giffen and Robert Loren Fleming chat 'Pro2Pro' about Ambush Bug, while John Byrne's She-Hulk smashes the fourth wall. Also: all-new interviews with cartoonists Fred Hembeck, Alan Kupperberg, Flaming Carrot's Bob Burden, and that indie man of heartache, David Chelsea. Plus histories of Spider-Ham, Forbush-Man, Reid Fleming - World's Toughest Milkman, MAD magazine in the 1970s, and Marvel's MAD knockoffs. With art by and/or commentary from David Boswell, Dick DeBartolo, Tom DeFalco, Al Feldstein, Al Jaffe, Stan lee, Dave Sim, and more!

Pick up the second part of 'The Magic of Lee and Kirby,' featuring more on the co-creators of the Marvel Universe! Inside, there's a new interview by Bullpenner George Tuska, as he reflects on his days at Marvel in the 1960s, including working over Jack's layouts. There's a look at the differences between Jack Kirby and Steve Ditko's approaches, and Will Murray gives an in-depth examination of the creation of the Fantastic Four.

When you meet the love of your life at a bus stop in Disneyworld... where else do you marry her, but at the 'Happiest Place on Earth?' But who will marry them...? Goofy? Mickey? All this plus a shocking discovery that could mean THE END OF THE IMAGE UNIVERSE AS WE KNOW IT!!! Okay... maybe not, but this issue is jammed-packed with heart and soul and we dare you not to cry!!
name: Let's Do This

description: Chris Lankford, the newest addition to Special Operations' team of Minders, is in a bit of a bind. He pretty much blew his first assignment and now if the gunmen on his tail don't kill him, Tara Chace just might! Can the rookie pull it together before it's too late ?
name: Saddlebags, Part 3

description: Unless zombie gravedigger Gwen Dylan eats a dead person's brain once a month, she loses her memories. The trouble is, for the week following a feeding, she shares her head with the dead person's final thoughts and has to complete any unfinished business they've left behind. In this case, it involves solving the murder of "Dead Fred." Meanwhile, Gwen's friend Spot is finding it increasingly difficult to keep his secret life as a were-terrier from his coworkers...
name: The Dead of Night
